later code.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe opt log shows:\n- LoopSimplify
created a dedicated exit block.\n- LoopUnrollAndJam completely
unrolled-and-jammed loop %do.body2.\n- Then the pass crashes in
appendReversedLoopsToWorklist while building a worklist for loops.\nThe pipeline
is loop(invalidate<all>,loop-unroll-and-jam,loop-unroll-and-jam). The first
LoopUnrollAndJam pass modifies the loop nest (fully unrolling the middle loop).
The second invocation then attempts to build a traversal from a LoopNest, and
crashes.\n\nThe stack trace points to:\n-
llvm::appendReversedLoopsToWorklist(reverse(Loops), Worklist)\n- where Loops =
LN.getLoops() from the LoopNest analysis.\nThe assertion triggers when calling
L->begin()/end(), which internally checks the loop's validity. This typically
happens when a Loop object has been invalidated after structural changes but a
stale LoopNest still references it.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nIn
LoopUnrollAndJamPass::run, after performing transformations, the pass
unconditionally preserves LoopNestAnalysis:\n  auto PA =
getLoopPassPreservedAnalyses();\n  PA.preserve<LoopNestAnalysis>();\n  return
PA;\nHowever, LoopUnrollAndJam modifies the loop structure (e.g., fully unrolling
jammed loops). Preserving LoopNestAnalysis in that case is incorrect because the
cached LoopNest will reference old Loop objects that may have been invalidated.
When the second loop-unroll-and-jam pass runs, it reuses this preserved LoopNest,
leading to traversal of invalid Loop objects and the assertion failure in
getSubLoops/end().\n\nThus, the first transformation (complete unroll-and-jam of
%do.body2) invalidates the loop nest, and the incorrect preservation of
LoopNestAnalysis causes a stale LN to be used by the subsequent pass
invocation.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n- File:
llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/LoopUnrollAndJamPass.cpp\n- Lines: 465-466\n- Change:
Do not preserve LoopNestAnalysis when the pass made modifications. Either remove
the preservation entirely or guard it so that it is only preserved when the
function is unmodified (in which case the code already returns
PreservedAnalyses::all()).\n\nConcretely, remove:\n
PA.preserve<LoopNestAnalysis>();\nso that the returned PreservedAnalyses from
getLoopPassPreservedAnalyses() does not include LoopNestAnalysis, forcing it to
be recomputed for the next pass invocation.\n\nThis ensures the next pass builds
a fresh LoopNest reflecting the updated LoopInfo and avoids traversing invalid
Loop objects.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe crash is caused by erroneously preserving
LoopNestAnalysis after loop transformations in LoopUnrollAndJamPass::run.
Removing the preservation of LoopNestAnalysis when changes occur will force
recomputation of the loop nest and prevent traversal of invalid Loop objects,
fixing the assertion. This aligns with the principle that assertion failures
indicate earlier logical errors\u2014in this case, incorrect analysis
preservation after IR/loop structural changes.",
